function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(word -> isuppercase(first(word)), words)
end
```
This function uses the `filter` method to iterate over the list of words and remove any words that do not start with a capital letter. The `isuppercase` function checks if the first character of the word is an uppercase letter, and the `first` function extracts the first character of the word.
